<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="C" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Chstise" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Chástise,</orth> 1) to punish severely: <bibl n="shak. tmp 5.263" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. V, 263</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 2.117" default="NO" valid="yes">John II, 117</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 5.2.84" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2, 84</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 2.3.104" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 II, 3, 104</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 1.5.12" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A I, 5, 12</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 4.4.331" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 IV, 4, 331</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 5.5.4" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. V, 5, 4</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 1.32" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. I, 32</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 5.2.54" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. V, 2, 54</bibl>.<lb />2) to reprimand, to set to rights: <cit><quote>that I may c. with the valour of my tongue all that impedes thee from the golden round,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mac 1.5.26" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. I, 5, 26</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>